# Variable Function

## Brief Description
The variable function is an important tool in the R programming language used to assign values to variables. It is used to store object names and values, and to allow them to be referenced later in the code.

## What Package Contains It
The variable function is a built-in feature of the R programming language, and is not part of any specific package.
